15/11/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- KFOR troops and the Kosovo Police Service (KPS) are monitoring the security situation in the province amid media reports about the Albanian National Army resurfacing. 
KFOR and KPS officials said at a press conference Wednesday (November 14th) they are investigating the activities of illegal groups operating in Kosovo. 
They also said they have contingency plans for any situation that may occur. 
(RTK, RFE, Tanjug, Balkanweb, RTS - 14/11/07)
